OTP Falls 1st Day in 4 as Hungary’s Quarterly Growth Halts

-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 
2011-08-16T15:31:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-16/otp-falls-as-hungarian-economic-growth-halts-in-second-quarter.html
OTP Bank Nyrt. Hungary’s largest
lender, fell the first day in four after data showed the economy
stopped growing in the second quarter and expansion in the
country’s largest export market,  Germany , almost stalled.  The shares dropped 3.4 percent to 4,300 forint as of the 5
p.m. end of trading in Budapest, extending this month’s decline
to 21 percent, the biggest slide since February 2009.  OTP led the benchmark BUX index 2.8 percent lower to
18,321.89, snapping three days of gains.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest 
 agergely@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  